            <li> I get vacation: I go for 3 months and travel through Australia and go here and there work on farms and somewhere where people are needed. The main thing is not in my job for others than my current company. </li>
            <li> I have to leave the company: I may only start the trip later and then go to Australia for longer. Find me in a big city for 2-3 months in my job to fill my rice base a little better and then go on trips. In addition, I could already explore the area for my workplace. </li>
        </ol>
        <p> When I was back from my vacation from the USA in mid -June, the second part of my father saying &rsquo;2. When you think. On the way to riding lessons, Sam then revealed to me that she decided to leave Ireland in early October. Bang. The next blow. She continued that the trip does not go directly to a new home, but similar to me, but would make a 3-month trip through New Zealand. She also said that she wanted to travel over the two main islands for the first 40 days with a camper van to visit the area. </p>
        <p> It all sounded interesting. Nevertheless, I didn't think it was very great that even my favorite travel companion here in Ireland would also go away. Many other friends are already back or will also go in the next few weeks. </p>
        <p> The next day I spoke to my superior again about Australia and revealed my idea again to go either this year in October or otherwise next year. Since his statements were still vague on the subject of unpaid vacation, we first stated that I decided for myself when I would go to Australia. </p>
        <p> This question was not too difficult to answer. Many of my best friends are already gone or go by October this year. So the time is almost perfect when I already go this year. Another idea came to me. Sam wants pretty much in the same direction as me and New Zealand should come on the travel schedule anyway if I have to give up my job. Why don't you fly directly to New Zealand. Rent a camper van and explore the islands for a few days. After about 2 weeks I could fly directly from Christchurch to Sydney. With this change of plan, I would even save a flight. So I now threw my original plan over the heap and planned the trip to New Zealand directly. </p>
        <p> On the last Tuesday I applied for my visa online and I was also approved immediately and directly. I only thought that quickly because I always read online beforehand that it takes at least 2 days to 4 weeks until the visa is approved. Incidentally, it cost almost &euro; 240. To start the visa, I now have to enter Australia by 09.07.2013. The working holiday year starts when entering. </p>
